# Networking & port publishing

Real apps talk вЂ” web to DB, world to service. Two questions, in the **Networks + Ports** corner.

## The model

A container gets its own **network namespace** (interfaces, IP, routes, firewall) plugged into a host **bridge**.

## Two moving parts

- **Networks вЂ” containerв†”container.** Same **user-defined bridge** в†’ resolve each other by `--name` (DNS), no `-p`. Drivers: `bridge` (~99%), `host`, `none`, `overlay`, `macvlan`.
- **Ports вЂ” worldв†’container.** Private by default; **publish** with `-p host:container` (an iptables rule underneath).

```
outside в”Ђв–є host:8080 в”Ђв–є[ -p ]в”Ђв–є container:80
api в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв–є db   (by name, same bridge)
```

Pick the network, find containers by name, publish safely, know what `-p` really does.
